// ./riolkus-mock-ccc-s5-keen-keener-multiset.yml #include "bits/stdc++.h" using namespace std; using ll = long long; const ll INF = 0x3f3f3f3f, LLINF = 0x3f3f3f3f3f3f3f3f; struct node { int val, cnt; node comb(const node o) const { return {val^o.val, cnt+o.cnt}; } }; const int MN = 262144; int N, Q, curXor = 0; #define MID int mid = (l+r)/2, lhs = i+1, rhs = i+(mid-l+1)*2 node seg[MN*2]; node update(int q, int v, int lev=17, int i=1, int l=0, int r=MN-1) { if (l > q || r < q) return seg[i]; if (l == q && r == q) return seg[i] = seg[i].comb({v, 1}); MID; if ((curXor >> lev) & 1) swap(lhs, rhs); seg[i] = update(q, v, lev-1, lhs, l, mid).comb(update(q, v, lev-1, rhs, mid+1, r)); return seg[i]; } node query(int ql, int qr, int lev=17, int i=1, int l=0, int r=MN-1) { if (l > qr || r < ql) return {0, 0}; if (l >= ql && r <= qr) return seg[i]; MID; if ((curXor >> lev) & 1) swap(lhs, rhs); return query(ql, qr, lev-1, lhs, l, mid).comb(query(ql, qr, lev-1, rhs, mid+1, r)); } int main() { ios_base::sync_with_stdio(false); cin.tie(NULL); cin >> N >> Q; while (N--) { int x; cin >> x; update(x, x); } while (Q--) { int T, a; cin >> T >> a; if (T == 1) update(a, a ^ curXor); else if (T == 2) { int b, c; cin >> b >> c; assert(a == 0 && b == 500000); curXor ^= c; } else { int b; cin >> b; auto p = query(a, b); if (p.cnt & 1) p.val ^= curXor; cout << p.val << '\n'; } } return 0; }
